para_trans: Shri Dhondiba Gaikwad, Tehsildar, posting of Tahsildar cadre officers awaiting appointment
GOVERNMENT ORDER NO. CHANGE-2025 / P.S. 152 / E-3
Madam Kama Marg, Martyr Rajguru Chowk,
Reference: - The Maharashtra Regulation of Transfer of Government Employees and Prevention of Delays in the discharge of Government Duties Act, 2005

The officers mentioned in the table below, awaiting appointment to the Tahsildar cadre, are listed in front of their names in column No. The post indicated in section 4 is being posted for administrative reasons with the approval of the competent authority in the interest of public service and administrative convenience.

The said order is with immediate effect and the aforesaid officer has issued an order vide Column No. Immediately join the position of the post mentioned in section 4. The concerned officer should immediately inform the Government by email / post at the date of his / her appearance at the place of posting given to him / her.

The officer concerned shall take care of joining the place of posting within the prescribed period as per the rules of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Period of assumption of office, Non-Service and Provisions during periods of suspension, dismissal and removal from service) Rules, 1981. Those concerned should note that if they do not otherwise join the position of the incumbent, their period of absence will count as "senate" (die non).

4. Leave shall not be granted to the officer concerned for any reason except with the previous sanction of the Government. Also, as per Rule-30 (c) of the Maharashtra Civil Services (Leave) Rules, 1981, no leave applications of officers transferred by the original office shall be entertained. such an application.
If received, they must be returned to the relevant authorities by post, registered at the original address.

5. In case of non-acquisition of post immediately in accordance with the said order or attempt to cancel transfer under any kind of pressure, the said action shall be governed by the Maharashtra Civil Services (Conduct) Rules.
Those concerned should note that being in violation of Rule 23 of 1979, disciplinary action will be taken against them as it is misconduct.
6. This Government Order is available on the website of the Government of Maharashtra www.maharashtra.gov.in.
